## Doc rules

- **One doc per product area** — before creating a new doc, check the CU Projects folder. If one exists for this area, update it.
- **What's Missing is a live view** — reflects current active gaps only. When a wave completes, its block moves to Learnings.
- **Problem and Decision are per wave** — when a wave closes they move to Learnings, main doc shows current wave only.
- **Inputs & Decisions is append-only** — never delete existing entries. New entries go at the bottom with date, person, source.
- **Bridge To-Dos are not CU tasks** — @mentions in the doc only. Bridge assigns manually.
- **Build and SEO run in parallel** — Launch is blocked until both are done.
- **Bridge QA happens after dev build, before launch** — dev posts "ready for QA" on the CU task, bridge reviews via QA Excel.
- **Jira task description must always include the CU task link** so dev knows where to post the ready-for-QA comment.

---

## What's Missing format

Per task, use `###` heading with CU task link and dev name, checkboxes with no blank line between heading and list:

```
### [Task name (MO-XXXXX)](https://app.clickup.com/t/9003000798/MO-XXXXX) · Dev: [name or "not assigned"]
- [x] Copy
- [ ] Build & QA — [status]
- [ ] Bridge QA
- [ ] Metadata / SEO Review — [status] ([owner])
- [ ] Launch
```

For phased projects (e.g. Industry Pages), group by phase: Phase 1, Phase 2, Phase 3 — each with its own Bridge QA.

---

## When fetching CU data

- Fetch task details: title, description, assignees, status, subtasks with their statuses and assignees
- Fetch comments for Inputs & Decisions
- Convert timestamps to YYYY-MM-DD dates
- Only include comments that contain decisions, key information, or blockers — skip automated bot comments and routine pings
- If a task cannot be fetched, flag it with ⚠ and note to re-run

---

## Output behaviour

- Always show the result for review before pushing to CU
- When pushing to CU, update the existing page — do not create a new one unless explicitly creating a new project
- Save local md files in `docs/examples/[project-folder]/`
- Never change Problem, Decision, or Bridge Checklist unless there is clearly new information that requires it
- Do not change Inputs & Decisions entries that already exist — append only
